<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-10-19T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-10-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="1291" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1291">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 855.48/5</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PWH1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Page</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <dateline>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-10-19">
                                <hi rend="italic">October 19, 1914</hi>.</date>
                        </dateline>
                        <p rend="center">[Telegram]</p>
                        <p>341. Telegram from Embassy Berlin 17th instant states that German
                            Government approves of plan to supply the population of Belgium with
                            food. You are authorized therefore to proceed on lines of your 786
                            [783], October 6.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>